commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Nabi will open the attack
Nabi to Kohli, no run, flighted delivery on off, Kohli makes room and pushes it to the off-side
Nabi to Kohli, 1 run, tossed up on off, driven down to long-on for a single
Nabi to du Plessis, no run, flighted delivery around off, du Plessis goes back and turns it to square leg
Nabi to du Plessis, 1 run, tossed up on middle, punched down to long-on for a single
Nabi to Kohli, 1 run, Nabi drifts one on middle and leg, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single

Nabi to du Plessis, FOUR, cracking shot, and a fumble at mid-off gets du Plessis going - backed away early and then punched one off the back-foot, to the left of the fielder who slid and let the ball go through, 7 off the first over
Gerald Coetzee, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Kohli, no run, short of a good length and well wide of off, Kohli throws his hands on the cut and misses
A slip in place for Coetzee
Gerald Coetzee to Kohli, no run, short of a good length and at the stumps, Kohli swings across the line and misses
Gerald Coetzee to Kohli, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, Kohli pushes forward and inner halves the drive to mid-on, off for a quick single
Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, du Plessis leans forward and toe-ends the push to cover
Fine leg comes in, square leg goes back - some disturbance and du Plessis pulls out at the last moment
Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, no run, short of a good length and jagging back into the right-hander, burst past du Plessis's inside edge and rolled off the thigh-pad

Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, SIX, cheeky and six, fine leg was inside the ring and this is du Plessis's go-to shot - shuffles across, used Coetzee's pace and then lapped it over, high and into the crowd at long leg
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah to Kohli, no run, back of a length and at the stumps, Kohli backs away and miscues the pull to mid-wicket

Bumrah to Kohli, no run, appeal for LBW, but this was sliding down leg, was very full and shaped back into the right-hander - a mini-shuffle as Kohli tried to flick and missed, struck in front of leg-stump
Bumrah to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Kohli, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! This was coming - Kohli was looking very shaky, tries to go after Bumrah and perishes in the process, short of a good length and shaping back into the right-hander, Kohli swings across the line, the ball catches the inside edge and Ishan Kishan completes a fine catch, diving to his left. The edge was audible and umpire Nitin Menon's finger went up in a flash, a rare failure for Kohli and RCB lose an early wicket. Kohli c Ishan Kishan b Bumrah 3(9)
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Will Jacks, no run, low full-toss outside off, Jacks is early into the drive and is beaten, sneaks under and bounces through to Ishan Kishan

Bumrah to Will Jacks, FOUR, beautifully played, full and into the pads, Jacks gets inside the line and then flicks it backward of square on the on-side, splits the two fielders in the deep to perfection - first runs of the IPL for Jacks

Bumrah to Will Jacks, no run, excellent comeback from Bumrah - slipped in the slower short ball on off, Jacks was static in the crease as he wasfted at that and missed, could've so easily dragged it back onto his stumps, on the bounce to the keeper
Kohli vs Bumrah in IPL 95 balls 140 runs Five dismissals SR 147.36
Akash Madhwal, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, punched square on the off-side for a single

Akash Madhwal to Will Jacks, FOUR, clubbed, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, Jacks picks the length early and then swings through the line, high and over mid-on, bounces away to the ropes
Akash Madhwal to Will Jacks, no run, short of a good length and on off - Jacks backs away and flat-bats the drive to mid-off
Will Jacks in T20 cricket \nOpening: Avg 31.68 | SR 161 | 3 X 100s | 28 X 50s \nMiddle order: Avg 19.78 | SR 141 | 2 X 50s
Akash Madhwal to Will Jacks, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Akash Madhwal to Will Jacks, out Caught by Tim David!! Caught at mid-on - RCB have lost two early, back of a length and at the stumps, Jacks backs away on the pull, struck it crisply, but he's hit it straight and flat, a straightforward catch to mid-on where David takes it with glee. Started well and showed some intent, but it's all too brief though. Will Jacks c Tim David b Akash Madhwal 8(6) [4s-2]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Akash Madhwal to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, nicely played, short of a good length and at the hips, Patidar gets inside the line, uses Madhwal's pace and clips it fine, beats the fielder in the ring and runs away to the ropes
Akash Madhwal to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, punched off the back-foot to deep point for a single
Gerald Coetzee [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, no run, fuller length delivery and seaming away from off, draws Patidar into a loose waft and beats him on the outside edge
Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, Coetzee shortens the length and angles one back into the right-hander, squirted off the inside edge and bounces past the leg-stump, rolling through to long leg
Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, no run, banged in short by Coetzee - du Plessis ducks under and then lets it go
Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, no run, back of a length and well wide of off, du Plessis gets on top of the bounce and cuts it to cover-point's right, an excellent diving stop to prevent a boundary

Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, SIX, clattered, on a good length and well wide of off - du Plessis stays deep in the crease, throws his hands on the drive and smacks it over mid-off, went flat and skimmed over the ropes

Gerald Coetzee to du Plessis, no run, appeal for a caught behind, but MI ain't convinced and they decide against a review. On a good length and following du Plessis as he backed away, a definite noise as the right-hander flicked and missed, but it came off the pad
Akash Madhwal to Rajat Patidar, no run, short of a good length and at the body, pushed back at the bowler

Akash Madhwal to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, lovely, back of a length and at the stumps, Patidar swivels across, lets the ball come and then plays the half-arm jab, up and over mid-on, bounces away to the ropes
Akash Madhwal to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, punched off the back-foot and to the left of cover for a single

Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, no run, short of a good length and skidding onto the right-hander, du Plessis backed away on the slog and got a thick in side edge back onto his box - he's down and in pain, takes some time to compose himself and he's then back on his feet
Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, no run, fuller length delivery on off, du Plessis hammers the drive to mid-off
Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, FOUR, drilled, half-volley on off, du Plessis clears his left leg and then drives it straight of mid-off, one bounce and over the ropes
Powerplay summary -- Nabi bowls a tight first over -- Kohli dismissed for 3 by Bumrah (2.3) -- Madhwal gets rid of Jacks for 8 (3.4) -- Faf and Patidar play some cracking shots
Shreyas Gopal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, the wrong 'un from Shreyas, Patidar rocks back and pulls it past square leg for a single

Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 3 runs, that was close, flighted delivery on off, du Plessis backed away and then punched it uppishly, went to Hardik's right and wasn't too far away, there's an overthrow at the striker's end as the return deflects off the stumps, allowing a 3rd
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, nudged past square leg for a single

Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 2 runs, tossed up on middle and leg, du Plessis backs away and drags a thick inside edge on the hoick, calls for the second and Rajat Patidar has to hurry, a better throw might've had him struggling
Shreyas Gopal vs RCB 7 matches 14 wickets Avg 11.14 ER 6.50 SR 10.3 Best 4/16
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 2 runs, the wrong 'un from Shreyas - spins back into the right-hander and du Plessis tucks it into the gap past square leg, comes back for the second
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, Shreyas tosses one well outside off, driven down to long-off for a single, 10 off the over
Pacers in Powerplay in night games at Wankhede this IPL \n17 overs | 8 wickets | Avg 15.88 | SR 12.8 | ER 7.47
Romario Shepherd, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Shepherd to du Plessis, 1 run, slower short ball from Shepherd - du Plessis backs away and whips it in the air, the ball bouncing short of the fielder at deep square leg
Shepherd to Rajat Patidar, leg byes, 1 run, short of a length and at the body, Patidar was shaping to pull and missed, struck high on the pad and dropped to the off-side

Shepherd to du Plessis, FOUR, classy, some sublime batting from du Plessis - hint of width outside off, he stays leg-sided and then flat-bats the drive, places it wide of mid-off and the ball races away
Shepherd to du Plessis, 1 run, slower short ball outside off - du Plessis backs away and chops it over cover-point for a single
Shepherd to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, back of a length and at the stumps, heaved away behind square on the on-side and it needed a sliding effort from Madhwal to prevent the boundary

Shepherd to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, drilled, back of a length and well wide of off, was the slower ball from Shepherd, but he's provided width and Patidar doesn't miss out - gets on top of the bounce and clatters it over mid-off, one bounce and over the ropes
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, dragged over the non-striker's head with the shovel, a single to long-on
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, no run, loopy delivery on off, Patidar swipes hard and loses his shape on the slog, drags a thick inside edge past the leg-stump
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, no run, the wrong 'un from Shreyas - Patidar backs away and can't beat backward point with the cut
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, SIX, massive, tossed up invitingly on off, Patidar gets under it on the slog-sweep, sends it soaring - high and deep into the stands at mid-wicket
Shreyas Gopal to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, Shreyas tosses one on off, Patidar can't resist and looks to repeat the slog-sweep, drags an inside edge, behind square on the on-side for a single

Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, the wrong 'un from Shreyas - du Plessis doesn't spot it, was looking to shovel it back over the bowler's head, drags it off the inner half and to the right of long-on

Time for the strategic break. A decent recovery from RCB after losing two early wickets. du Plessis looks determined and Rajat Patidar is playing some lovely shots, they'll have to take this partnership deep and set-up a platform for the firepower of Maxwell, Lomror and DK to finish well
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Hardik Pandya to du Plessis, no run, short of a good length and well wide of off, du Plessis throws his hands on the cut and missed
Hardik Pandya to du Plessis, no run, on a length and just outside off - du Plessis went hard on the drive and mistimed it to cover
Hardik Pandya to du Plessis, 1 run, short of a good length and well wide of off, cut crisply and straight to the fielder at deep cover

Hardik Pandya to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, hammered, back of a length and well wide of off, Patidar gets on top of the bounce and clatters it wide of cover - long-off gets around and keeps them down to a couple

Hardik Pandya to Rajat Patidar, SIX, beautifully played, on a good length and just outside off - Patidar gets forward, swings through the line and sends it sailing, high and deep into the stands at wide long-on
Hardik Pandya to Rajat Patidar, wide, Hardik attempts the slower ball and spills it miles outside off - called as a wide
Hardik Pandya to Rajat Patidar, wide, another slower ball from Hardik, but this is once again past the tramlines, called as a wide
Hardik Pandya to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, short of a good length and wide of off, sliced away to the left of backward point, a slight fumble and they're back for the second, 13 off the over
Bumrah back for a second over
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-4-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to du Plessis, 1 run, low full-toss on the pads, whipped down to long-on for a single
Bumrah to Rajat Patidar, no run, banged in short and just outside off - Patidar backs away and then thinks about ramping it past the keeper, decides against and lets it go
Bumrah to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off - Patidar slogs without any timing and the ball rolls down to long-on
Bumrah to du Plessis, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed into the gap square past cover for a single

Bumrah to Rajat Patidar, no run, banged in short and angling into the right-hander, Patidar looks clumsy as he tried to drop his gloves at the last moment. An appeal for caught behind, it ain't given and MI have reviewed. Did the ball flick the glove on its way to the keeper? No, a flat line on UltraEdge and umpire Nitin Menon's original call stays - MI have lost a review
Bumrah to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, a cracking yorker from Bumrah, right at the base of middle - Patidar jams his bat down and squeezes it to the off-side
Gerald Coetzee [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, SIX, Patidar is in some form tonight - low full-toss and he's picked the bones off it, shovels it high and over mid-wicket, the ball dropping over the ropes for a maximum

Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, SIX, back-to-back sixes for Patidar, brings up his fifty as well, length ball at the stumps, he leans forward and then sends it whistling into the stands at wide mid-wicket - a 25-ball half-century
First 50-plus score for an RCB batter other than Kohli in IPL 2024
Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Coetzee gets his man now - banged in short and angling into the body, Patidar was shaping to pull off the front-foot, he's slightly rushed onto the shot, the ball popping off the glove and lobbing into the hands of Ishan Kishan. Patidar walks off to a good reception though, he's played his hand in setting up RCB tonight. Rajat Patidar c Ishan Kishan b Gerald Coetzee 50(26) [4s-3 6s-4]
Glenn Maxwell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Maxwell, no run, short and into the rib-cage, Maxwell is cramped for room and the ball drops off his thigh-pad onto the off-side
Gerald Coetzee to Maxwell, wide, the bouncer from Coetzee, but it's too short and too high, called as a wide
Gerald Coetzee to Maxwell, wide, another short ball, but it's down leg and it's way too high as well, back-to-back wides from Coetzee
Gerald Coetzee to Maxwell, no run, fuller length delivery on off, Maxwell stays on the back-foot and pushes it to mid-off
Gerald Coetzee to Maxwell, no run, back of a length and just outside off, pushed off the back-foot to cover
Shreyas Gopal [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, flatter and at the pads, whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Shreyas Gopal to Maxwell, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Shreyas Gopal to Maxwell, out Lbw!! Another failure for Maxwell and he walks away in disappointment - was the wrong 'un and he didn't spot it, was shuffling across and tried to flick it onto the on-side, missed it completely and is struck bang in front of off - the ball was going on and crashing into the middle-stump, easy call for umpire Nitin Menon and Maxwell doesn't bother to ponder about a review either. Maxwell lbw b Shreyas Gopal 0(4)
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, no run, DK attempts the reverse sweep, did he get an inside edge? Might have been, MI think and decide against a review - a strange shot first ball, was shaping to get it into the gap behind square on the off-side
Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, no run, the wrong 'un now, DK went right back on the flick and missed, would've been sliding down leg
Most ducks in IPL 17 D Karthik/ Rohit Sharma/ G Maxwell * 15 Rashid Khan/ P Chawla/ S Narine/ Mandeep Singh 14 M Pandey/ A Rayudu
Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, 1 run, another wrong 'un, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 2 runs, tossed up on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side and he's back for the second

They've called for the strategic break. RCB were looking good, but they've lost two on the bounce once again and will need to repair the innings. du Plessis looks poised though, he'll have to bat deep and take his team to a fighting score
Romario Shepherd [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Shepherd to Karthik, 1 run, full outside off, DK flicks it into the gap to the right of mid-wicket
Shepherd to du Plessis, 1 run, gets the yorker length at the pads, clipped away to the right of deep square
Shepherd to Karthik, 1 run, short and wide of off, didn't have the pace DK was looking for and hence, he slices the cut to the left of sweeper cover
Shepherd to du Plessis, FOUR, overpitches the I0$ full delivery and du Plessis bends his back knee to slam it up and over extra cover for a one-bounce boundary...
Shepherd to du Plessis, 1 run, first IPL fifty this season for skipper Faf. Gets there with a pull to deep mid-wicket and the dressing room looks a happy bunch...

Shepherd to Karthik, 2 runs, short of length angled into the pads, DK swivels and pulls to the left of deep square where Madhwal puts in a commendable diving effort to pull the ball back inches inside the rope
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, makes room and stabs the quicker delivery to deep cover
Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, 1 run, quicker and straighter, DK pulls into the mid-wicket pocket
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, SIX, Shreyas Gopal goes full and serves it in the slot for Faf who made room early to tonk it over long-on for an 88-metre maximum
Shreyas Gopal to du Plessis, 1 run, he goes fast and flat outside off now, Faf transfers his weight onto the back foot and mistimes the loft to the left of long-off. Goes on the bounce to the fielder
Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, no run, slower and wider of off, DK moves a long way across and fails to get bat on ball on the attempted sweep. Struck on the front pad, but the impact was well outside off
Shreyas Gopal to Karthik, no run, once again slows the pace and drags it wide of off, DK's early into his slog and gets beaten on the under edge

Highlights (Overs 7-15) -- 86/2 -- Patidar hits counterattacking fifty off 25 balls -- MI lose a review for caught-behind (10.5) -- Bumrah bowls a quiet over amid the onslaught -- Coetzee removes Patidar for 50 (11.3) -- Gopal traps Maxwell LBW for a duck (12.2) -- Faf gets to fifty off 33 balls (13.5) -- Gopal bowls out with 1/32
Akash Madhwal [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack

Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, wide, I0$ low full toss spilled wide of the tramline outside off, Faf shoulders arms. MI have reviewed this. Faf didn't move much and the ball was clearly a shade outside off. The onfield call stays...
Akash Madhwal to du Plessis, 1 run, goes full and wide once again, du Plessis mistimes the drive to the left of mid-off

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, FOUR, that's not ABD folks, it's DK. Goes deep inside the crease and past his off-stump, waits for something full and he's helped the full toss with a gentle ramp-like scoop fine of the third man fence...

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, no run, DK looks to repeat the dose and Akash Madhwal was smart enough to fire the I0$ well wide of off. Had DK stayed in his normal stance, it would have been a wide. Not to be. He went searching for the ball and ended up taking a blow on his boot...
Akash Madhwal to Karthik, FOUR, and again! DK wants to toy with the field it appears. He camps back and moves outside off to slice the scoop between the keeper and the short third fielder....

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, FOUR, has someone told DK that only runs behind the keeper counts? He shuffles outside off, goes deep inside the crease and slices the full and wide delivery to the right of the keeper. Coetzee, at short third, dives and gets a hand but he only succeeds in palming it away to the fine leg fence...
Akash Madhwal to Karthik, wide, Akash Madhwal goes full and well wide of off, DK stays his ground and lets it pass

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, FOUR, oh my! 4 boundaries in the same region. This one's come off the thick outside edge, but RCB and DK won't mind one bit. He goes hard at a full and wide delivery and the edge flies down to the third man fence, beating the fielder to his left in the blink of an eye...19 runs off the over.
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to du Plessis, 2 runs, I0$ full toss on the stumps, Faf looks to heave down the ground and drags it off the thick inside half to the left of long-on

MI are claiming a catch and umpire Nitin Menon has gone upstairs. The review is for a fair catch. Nothing on the UltraEdge. No bat involved and the sound was off the bat hitting the ground. Not out. It's an umpire's review (as he thought there was bat on it), so MI won't lose the review.

Bumrah to du Plessis, byes, 1 run, Bumrah goes full and wide of off, Faf looks to biff straight down the ground and misses. Ishan Kishan dives across to his left and claims the catch. He tosses the ball towards the mid-on and ends up conceding a single instead...
Bumrah to Karthik, 1 run, very full on the stumps, DK jams the drive to long-on
Bumrah to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to du Plessis, out Caught by Tim David!! Excellent catch by Tim David. Faf mistimes the full toss off the splice and David comes running in from long-on to time the slide to absolute perfection. He also had to maintain his balance after the slide and took the catch inches above the turf. Top stuff. du Plessis c Tim David b Bumrah 61(40) [4s-4 6s-3]
Last four innings for Du Plessis at Wankhede: 73*, 44, 65 & 61
Mahipal Lomror given out lbw and he is holding his toe and grimacing in pain. No bat involved confirms the UltraEdge. Umpire's call on hitting. Gone!
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Bumrah to Lomror, out Lbw!! Jasprit Bumrah is on a hat-trick. Goes for the toe-crushing yorker and Lomror had no time to react. Tried to defend/push into the on-side but the ball dipped and clonked him on the front toe in line with middle and leg. Finger went up straightaway and Lomror took a chance with the review as he felt it might sneak down leg, not to be. Lomror lbw b Bumrah 0(1)
Here's the impact sub Saurav Chauhan
Saurav Chauhan, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Bumrah to Saurav Chauhan, 1 run, oh dear! No hat-trick but that was a good delivery from Jasprit Bumrah. Yorker length aiming for the base of middle and leg, Saurav Chauhan manages to clip it off the cue end to the left of deep square. 5 runs and 2 wickets off the over.
Gerald Coetzee [3.0-0-28-1] is back into the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Saurav Chauhan, no run, gee, this yorker business has gone infectious it appears. Gerald Coetzee nails the yorker from round the wicket and Saurav Chauhan can only jam it down the pitch..
He switches to over the wicket now...
Gerald Coetzee to Saurav Chauhan, FOUR, tries for the yorker again and slips a low full toss outside off, Chauhan slices the drive behind point and that's a much-needed boundary for RCB...
Gerald Coetzee to Saurav Chauhan, wide, loses radar and spills a I0$ full delivery down leg, Chauhan looks to help it away to fine leg, but no dice...
Gerald Coetzee to Saurav Chauhan, 1 run, skiddy short of length delivery pitched outside leg, Chauhan swivels and pulls square on the leg-side
Gerald Coetzee goes round the wicket now...
Gerald Coetzee to Karthik, 1 run, a I0$ hit-me full toss on the pads, DK was perhaps anticipating something short and hence couldn't connect cleanly on the flick. Down to fine leg for a single
Gerald Coetzee to Saurav Chauhan, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, Chauhan slices the lofted drive to the right of sweeper cover who collects it on the bounce

Gerald Coetzee to Karthik, SIX, this was the type of delivery DK anticipated earlier (4th ball of the over). It was short and outside leg stump, DK swivels and helps the pull into the fine leg stands. Easy as you like. 14 off the over
Bumrah to Saurav Chauhan, no run, I0$ bumper on the stumps, hurries Chauhan for pace and beats him on the pull. I1$
Bumrah to Saurav Chauhan, 2 runs, I0$ full and wide of off, Chauhan toe-ends the loft over the backtracking mid-on fielder and comes hustling back to complete the second...
Bumrah to Saurav Chauhan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Saurav Chauhan, out Caught by Akash Madhwal!! Wicket number four for Jasprit Bumrah. He digs it short and angles it into the batter, Chauhan goes for the pull but it's (the pace) too hot to handle and he's top-edged that to the fielder at mid-wicket. Akash Madhwal couldn't have asked for an easier catch than that. Saurav Chauhan c Akash Madhwal b Bumrah 9(8) [4s-1]
Vijaykumar Vyshak, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Vijaykumar Vyshak, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Vijaykumar Vyshak, out Caught by Nabi!! Number five for Bumrah and he's on a hat-trick once again. Goes for the back of a length and extracts extra bounce off the turf. Vijaykumar Vyshak came dancing down the wicket in search of something full, but instead got a ball that hurried onto his bat from a shorter length. Heaves and toe-ends it straight to Nabi at mid-off for catching practice. Vijaykumar Vyshak c Nabi b Bumrah 0(1)
Akash Deep, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Akash Deep, 1 run, Akash Deep denies the hat-trick. Bumrah nails the yorker and it's been squeezed off the toe end down to fine leg

Bumrah to Karthik, SIX, it's hit the ropes on the full. How badly RCB needed this? Bumrah goes full and wide of off, DK stays deep inside the crease and powers his wrists through the lofted drive that kisses the sweeper cover fence on the full... Bumrah ends with excellent figures of 5/21
First five-wicket haul vs RCB by any bowler. Previous best: 4/10 by Ashish Nehra for CSK in Bengaluru in 2015
Bowlers with two five-fers in IPL James Faulkner Jaydev Unadkat Bhuvneshwar Kumar Jasprit Bumrah
Akash Madhwal [3.0-0-38-1] is back into the attack
Akash Madhwal to Akash Deep, 1 run, Akash Madhwal bowls this full on leg stump, Akash Deep slogs off the toe-end to the right of deep square leg

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, no run, RCB have challenged the umpire's call here. For a height no-ball. It has not been given onfield. Looks slightly above the waist and the decision should come in favour of the batting side? DK smartly asked Akash Deep not to run for the single. He heaved the high full toss to the right of long-on and expected it to be a no ball but not to be. The telly umpire had a few looks and in fairness, it did look a bit 70-30 in favour of the batter...
Akash Madhwal to Karthik, wide, full and well wide of off, Karthik lets it pass
Akash Madhwal to Karthik, SIX, DK goes for the slice again and he's made a habit of flirting with the boundary ropes here. Once again the ball lands just over the ropes at square third man

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, SIX, he's smashed the bones out of this one. Short and into the body, DK swivels and slams the pull into the square leg stands with terrific timing. Gee, he's playing an absolute blinder here...

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, FOUR, Madhwal switches to the fuller length and DK's spanked that past the diving Hardik Pandya at mid-off to his left. That will be fifty for DK and the RCB dressing room absolutely cock-a-hoop at the moment

Akash Madhwal to Karthik, 1 run, heaves the fuller length delivery and gets it off the inside half to the right of deep square. no chance of a second there and they will have to be content with the single..19 runs off the over

21:32 local, 16:02 GMT: 52 runs off 3 non-Bumrah overs in the last 5 overs. And Bumrah just conceded 14 runs and picked up 4 wickets while at it. For MI, it was Jasprit Bumrah doing all the magic in the slog overs and for RCB, it was DK. If ever RCB needed a helluva knock from DK, this had to be it. He literally toyed with Akash Madhwal and gave him a night to forget as he pasted him to all corners of the ground. Before this game, Kohli was the only batter to get past 50 for RCB this season and this game saw 3 other batters (Faf, Patidar and DK) do it. All three special and unique in its own way. Can RCB take all this positivity and I0$ into their bowling? Back shortly for the reply...

Bumrah: It was a good day. One of those days where what I was executing was working. Wicket looked sticky (early on). Disappointed with my last ball. When the first over was bowled, I realised ball was gripping a bit. Wanted to bowl a good hard length. I've been doing this for 11 years, so I'm used to it. What happened at the end was dew set in and it got better to bat on. Don't want to get too high or too low with good and bad days. This game is a great leveller. Want to keep working hard. The wicket did get better. DK played a special knock. Over here, it's tough to stop someone when they get going.
